programme.title: Jurassic Park III
programme.desc: When a mysterious couple convinces Dr. Grant to take them to Isla Sorna, he later discovers that they have a hidden motive after they become stuck on the island with its deadly inhabitants.(n)

programme.title: Timeline
programme.desc: An unknown IT company builds a time-machine, and tests it by moving Professor Edward to 14-century France. A team is then formed including two students and an archaeologist, to travel through time to retrieve him. Will they be able to succeed on a mission that's the first of its kind.(n)

programme.title: Ride Along
programme.desc: As a way to prove himself worthy of marrying Angela, James' sister, security guard Ben joins her cop brother on a day long patrol of Atlanta.(n)

programme.title: Grosse Pointe Blank
programme.desc: Martin Blank combines business with personal affairs when he accepts a contract kill at the same suburb where his high school reunion is taking place. But once he arrives in Grosse Points, he finds himself pursued from all angles, whether by other assassins or by federal agents.(n)

programme.title: The Divergent Series: Allegiant
programme.desc: Tris and Four make the hard decision to leave their home behind in an attempt to find a way to save Chicago from turmoil. However, they end up being taken to a city of hidden secrets where they end up learning the backstory of how their world became what it is.(n)

programme.title: London Has Fallen
programme.desc: Following the mysterious death of the British Prime Minister, Secret Agent Mike Banning does all he can to stop the planned attack, targeting to assassinate all western world leaders attending the funeral.(n)

programme.title: Jurassic World
programme.desc: Two decades after the events of Jurassic Park, a new theme park is open for business, but history has a habit of repeating itself, when a transgenic dinosaur escapes from its enclosure and creates havoc on the island of Isla Nublar.(n)

programme.title: Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom
programme.desc: Four years after the Jurassic World theme park was closed down and the eruption of a dormant volcano on the island, Owen (Chris Pratt) and Claire (Bryce Dallas Howard) return to Isla Nubar to save the dinosaurs before they extinguish.(n)

programme.title: World War Z
programme.desc: United Nations employee, Gerry Lane (Brad Pitt), must leave his family and traverse the world in a race against time to stop a Zombie pandemic that is crumbling armies and governments in its wake.(n)

programme.desc: Set in a small Nigerian village that suffers the shortage of drinkable water, a conflict ensues between the militants and the government over the greed of the oil corporations, only to result in a ripple effect spanning the whole country and affecting the global oil industry.(n)

programme.desc: After a failed mission leaves him the lone survivor of his team of operatives, Ethan Hunt is accused of betraying his team and must fight to prove his innocence.(n)

programme.desc: In a future Chicago setting, people are divided into five distinct factions based on their personalities. Beatrice discovers that she is Divergent, meaning she does not fit into any one faction, and soon uncovers a sinister plot brewing in her seemingly perfect society.(n)

programme.title: The Ladykillers
programme.desc: A Southern professor who puts together a group of thieves to rob a casino. They rent a room in an old woman's house, but soon she discovers the plot and they must kill her, a task that is more difficult than it seems.(n)

programme.desc: Three children hire a bodyguard to protect them from the playground bully, who constantly torments them.(n)

programme.title: Hot Rod

programme.desc: When a music executive offers Josie and her struggling band a record deal, the band slowly discover that they've become part of a major conspiracy designed to brainwash teenagers through subliminal messages.(n)

programme.desc: When the ex-con Ray teams up with two of his buddies to plan a coin heist, things take an unexpected turn when his son Timmy steals the coins in an attempt to get his father's attention and teach him a valuable lesson along the way.(n)

programme.title: Be Cool

Chili depends on singer and songwriter Linda Moon's talents who asks him to help her cancel her contract with Nick Carr and Raji, who quickly become Chili's enemies.(n)
